{{Quote|I remember the brutality of the Cauldron. A privilege I paid for with much blood.|translated=1|Bowdaar|<ref name="Star Wars: The Old Republic: Knights of the Fallen Empire">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic: Knights of the Fallen Empire]]''</ref>}}
'''The Cauldron''' was a large [[Gladiator/Legends|gladiatorial]] arena on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Rattatak/Legends|Rattatak]]. The rocky world held many of these gladiator pits, though the Cauldron was the largest and most infamous, attracting the best combatants.

==History==
[[File:Blorga_cauldron.jpg|thumb|250px|right|The result of a fight in the Cauldron.]]
With warfare common across the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Rattatak/Legends|Rattatak]], an enterprising [[Rattataki/Legends|Rattataki]] hatched a lucrative scheme involving the creation of these [[Gladiator/Legends|gladiatorial]] pits. [[Gender/Legends|He]] would pit mercenaries and [[Slavery/Legends|slave]] [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] against one another in gladiatorial combat, and the [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] generated from the wagers would help purchase more soldiers and offworld weapons for the ongoing war. The blood-sport of Rattatak quickly evolved.

The Cauldron was located within a craggy spire of rock; a huge cavern ringed by a large number of viewing boxes. War barons and generals would attend the contests, to seek out the soldiers that would win them their wars. Slavers provided opposition for the gladiators, often in the form of dangerous offworld beasts or monsters trained to [[Death/Legends|kill]].

However, the Cauldron's deadliest gladiator was none of these. After the outbreak of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]] [[Mission to Rattatak|entered]] the Cauldron and killed [[Unidentified henchman (the Cauldron)|Dooku's henchman]] in the hope that the watching [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] would be impressed enough with her skill to make her his [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] apprentice. Ventress, armed with twin [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsabers]], made short work of the various gladiators the Cauldron threw at her&mdash;from blood-thirsty [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorreans]] to dangerous [[Wampa/Legends|wampa]] ice creatures. Ventress prevailed, and challenged Dooku himself on the arena floor. Ventress was bested, but Dooku nevertheless recruited her to his cause.

